    <h1>Traditional Food of India</h1>

    <!-- Dish 1: Biryani -->
    <div class="food-item">
        <h2>Biryani</h2>
        <img src="biryani.jpg" alt="Biryani" />
        <p>
            Biryani is a flavorful and aromatic rice dish that originated in India but is beloved worldwide. It is prepared by
            layering fragrant Basmati rice with marinated meat (usually chicken, lamb, or goat) or vegetables, and a blend of
            exotic spices, saffron, and herbs. The dish is slow-cooked, allowing the flavors to meld together, resulting in a
            delectable and mouthwatering treat.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Dish 2: Butter Chicken -->
    <div class="food-item">
        <h2>Butter Chicken</h2>
        <img src="butter_chicken.jpg" alt="Butter Chicken" />
        <p>
            Butter Chicken, also known as Murgh Makhani, is a popular North Indian dish. It consists of succulent pieces of
            grilled chicken served in a creamy tomato-based sauce, flavored with spices like garam masala and fenugreek. This
            indulgent dish is best enjoyed with naan or steamed rice.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Dish 3: Masala Dosa -->
    <div class="food-item">
        <h2>Masala Dosa</h2>
        <img src="masala_dosa.jpg" alt="Masala Dosa" />
        <p>
            Masala Dosa is a classic South Indian delicacy loved by people all over the country. It is a thin, crispy rice and
            lentil crepe, typically filled with a spiced potato mixture. Served with coconut chutney and sambar (a flavorful
            lentil soup), Masala Dosa is a delightful and satisfying breakfast or snack option.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Dish 4: Rogan Josh -->
    <div class="food-item">
        <h2>Rogan Josh</h2>
        <img src="rogan_josh.jpg" alt="Rogan Josh" />
        <p>
            Rogan Josh is a Kashmiri curry known for its rich red color and tender meat, often lamb or goat. The dish is
            prepared with a blend of warming spices like cloves, cardamom, and cinnamon, along with red chili powder, giving it
            a mild to medium level of spiciness. The slow-cooked meat is cooked in yogurt-based gravy, resulting in a sumptuous
            and flavorsome delight.
        </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Dish 5: Gulab Jamun -->
    <div class="food-item">
        <h2>Gulab Jamun</h2>
        <img src="gulab_jamun.jpg" alt="Gulab Jamun" />
        <p>
            No Indian meal is complete without a sweet treat, and Gulab Jamun is a beloved dessert option. These soft and
            syrupy milk-based dumplings are deep-fried to golden perfection and then soaked in a fragrant sugar syrup infused
            with cardamom and rosewater. The result is a heavenly dessert that melts in your mouth and leaves you craving for
            more.
        </p>
    </div>

